\par \pard\plain \s26\sb120\sa120 \f5\fs20 {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst  title }{\fldrslt Visual Prolog}}'s BGI system does not restrict you to creating only graphics; you can also output text in a variety of fonts, sizes, and styles.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sa120 \f5\fs20 You output graphics text by calling either {\uldb\cf11 outtext}{\v outtext_1} or {\uldb\cf11 outtextxy}{\i\v outtextxy_3}; if clipping is On, all text strings output by {\uldb\cf11 outtext}{\v outtext_1} and {\uldb\cf11 
