. The screen image is stored in a string, so you can manipulate it as you do other variables, but you can't write it out or in
sert it into a database. This restriction exists because the screen image might contain several zeros (in other words, a NULL byte) which, to {\field\fldedit{\*\fldinst  title }{\fldrslt Visual Prolog}}, signifies the end of an output string or database.

