\par \pard\plain \s16\sa120 \f5\fs20 
The IBM 8514 Graphics Adapter and the VGA in 256K color mode are "RGB" (for "Red-Green-Blue") graphics cards. Both provide color palettes of 256 colors from a list of 256K colors; the palette colors are defined by numerous combinations of red, green, and 
blue.
\par The IBM 8514 graphics card is a new, hi-resolution graphics card capable of resolutions up to 1024 x 768 pixels. Its BGI d
river file name is IBM8514.BGI. The BGI autodetection logic can't properly detect the IBM 8514 graphics card; it will recognize the 8514 as a VGA in vgaHI mode. In order to use the IBM 8514 card, the {\i GrDriver} argument to {\b initgraph}
 must be bound to the value of ibm8514 (which is defined in BGI.CON) when your program initializes the BGI. With the IBM 8514, you should not call {\uldb\cf11 detectgraph}{\v detectgraph_2} (or {\uldb\cf11 initgraph}{\v initgraph_5} with {\i GrDriver}
 set to detect) unless you want to enter its lower-resolution VGA-emulation mode.
\par The supported modes of the IBM 8514 card are ibm8514LO (640x480 pixels), and ibm8514HI (1024x768 pixels). Both modes are defined as constants in BGI.CON.
\par The IBM 8514 uses three 6-bit values to define colors; each defined color has a 6-bit Red, Green, and Blue component. The {\uldb\cf11 setrgbpalette}{\v setrgbpalette_4} predicate enables you to define colors for the IBM 8514.
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-851\li851\sa120 \f5\fs20 {\b setrgbpalette}(INTEGER {\i Index, }INTEGER{\i  RedComp, }INTEGER{\i  GreenComp, }INTEGER{\i  BlueComp})
\par \pard\plain \s16\sa120 \f5\fs20 The {\i Index} argument defines the palette entry to be loaded; {\i Index} is an integer ranging from 0--255. The arguments {\i RedComp, GreenComp,} and {\i BlueComp}
 define the component colors of that palette entry. Only the lower byte of each of these values is used, and out of this byte, only the 6 most-significant bits are loaded into the palette.
\par \pard\plain \s26\sb120\sa120 \f5\fs20 {\b Restrictions on Using the 8514 Driver
\par }The other BGI palette-manipulation predicates--{\uldb\cf11 setallpalette}{\v setallpalette_1}, {\uldb\cf11 setpalette}{\v setpalette_2}, and {\uldb\cf11 getpalette}{\v getpalette_1}--can't be used with the IBM 8514 driver or with the VGA in 256K colo
r mode. For compatibility with the other IBM graphics adapters, the BGI driver (IBM8514.BGI) defines the first 16 palette entries of the IBM 8514 to the default colors of the EGA/VGA. These values can be used as is, or changed with the setrgbpalette predi
cate. The floodfill predicate does not work with the IBM 8514 driver or with the VGA in 256K color mode.
