\par To link the stroked character font file(s) into your executable, you need to use the {\uldb\cf11 bgifont}{\v bgifont_compiler_directive}{\i  }
compiler directive, and you need to give the public name for each font being linked in (see the following example).
\par To specify that the library BGI.LIB should be linked in, you must choose the Options/Link Options/Libraries menu item and give the path and name for the BGI library, such as c:\\prolog\\graphics\\bgi.
