\par {\b Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s16\sa120 \f5\fs20 {\b settextstyle} sets the text font, the direction in which text is displayed, and the size of the characters. A call to {\b settextstyle} affects all text output by {\b\uldb\cf11 outtext}{\b\v outtext_1} and {
\b\uldb\cf11 outtextxy}{\b\v outtextxy_3}.
\par The arguments {\i Font, Direction}, and {\i CharSize} passed to {\b settextstyle} have the following meanings:
\par Font: One 8x8 bit-mapped font and several "stroked" fonts are available. The 8x8 bit-mapped font is the default. Constant declarations defined in BGI.PRE provide names for the different font settings, as shown in the following table.
\par \pard\plain \s24\sb120\keep\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp60 \tx1418\tx2127 \b\f5\fs20\lang2057 Name\tab Value\tab Description
