\par small_FONT\tab 2\tab Stroked small font
\par sansserif_FONT\tab 3\tab Stroked sans-serif font
\par \pard \s25\qj\fi-2127\li2127\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \tx1701 gothic_FONT\tab 4\tab Stroked gothic font
\par \pard\plain \s26\sb120\sa120 \f5\fs20 
The default bit-mapped font is built into the graphics system. Stroked fonts are stored in *.CHR disk files, and only one is kept in memory at a time. Therefore, when you select a stroked font (different from the last selected stroked font), the correspon
ding *.CHR file must be loaded from disk. To avoid this loading when several stroked fonts are used, you can link font files into your program. You do this by registering them using the {\uldb\cf11 bgifont}{\v bgifont_compiler_directive}
 compiler directive.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sa120 \f5\fs20 {\i Direction}: Font directions supported are horizontal text (left to right) and vertical text (rotated 90 degrees counterclockwise). The default direction is {\i horiz_DIR}.
\par \pard\plain \s24\sb120\keep\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp60 \tx993\tx1843 \b\f5\fs20\lang2057 Name\tab Value\tab Description
