CharSize} = 0, only stroked characters are affected.
\par \pard \s32\fi-284\li284\sa60\tx284\tx567 {\f1 \'b7\tab }If {\i CharSize} = 1, {\b\uldb\cf11 outtext}{\b\v outtext_1} and {\b\uldb\cf11 outtextxy}{\b\v outtextxy_3}
 will display characters from the 8x8 bit-mapped font in an 8x8 pixel rectangle on the screen.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }If {\i CharSize} = 2, these output predicates will display characters from the 8x8 bit-mapped font in a 16x16 pixel rectangle; and so on (up to a limit of 10 times the normal size).
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }When {\i CharSize} = 0 (or {\i user_char_SIZE}, a constant defined in BGI.PRE), the output predicates {\b\uldb\cf11 outtext}{\b\v outtext_1} and {\b\uldb\cf11 outtextxy}{\b\v outtextxy_3}
